This paper involves the use of deep reinforcement learning for algorithmic trading, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). It also involves the use of sentiment analysis (cs.IR) and knowledge graphs (cs.SI) for better predictions. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of traditional time series data, which falls under the category of computational finance (cs.CE).
